	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Just out of curiosity I tried applying a delta-codec to the smb_orig pattern data and got a file that was 11956 bytes (that is, about 18% of the original file. or 73% if compared to a plain 2-bit represenation). It'd be interesting to try to implement the decoder in 6502 assembly sometime, since it's not very complex iirc (no multiplication/division needed).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
